e first three branches show what can happen to the radiation, and the last three branches indicate the changes that they induce in matter. This classification also allows quantitative characterization of the changes that result from the interaction. The changes in the particles of radiation can be mathematically described, assuming that the 85 Nuclear and Radiochemistry.},
