}
@book_section{Zhao2018,
   abstract = {High-κ and metal gate has been applied in 45-nm technology node to solve the problem of silicon-oxide-based gate dielectric and doped polycrystalline silicon gate electrode. It is well known that when the gate dielectric is scaled down to a thickness around 1 nm, the tunneling leakage through the dielectric increases to an unacceptable value, and the depletion layer formed in the polysilicon gate electrode and the dopant diffusion across the dielectric set a limit for further downscaling. The integration of high-κ/metal gate stacks is regarded as the most important technical revolution in CMOS technology after the introduction of the polysilicon gate in the 1960s. This chapter will give a technical review on the high-κ dielectric and metal gate, covering the limitation of the conventional gate stack using SiO2-based gate dielectric and polysilicon gate electrode, the benefits of high-κ and metal gate, and the current achievements in material selection, processing, and integration of high-κ dielectric and metal gate electrodes. Hafnium-based high-κ materials and compatible metal gate electrodes are discussed. An example of integration of the HfO2 high-κ dielectric with dual metal gate electrodes, TiN and TiAl, is introduced in detail, together with that of the all-ALD high-κ/metal gate stack for FinFTEs.},
